[6] Cholera - Malaysia
Date: Sun 1 Apr 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Star online [edited]
<http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2007/4/1/nation/20070401150804&sec=nation>

A cholera outbreak in 3 northern Sabah districts has occurred, with
dozens of patients suspected to be infected with _Vibrio cholerae_
already being discharged from hospitals.
The outbreak that began about 3 weeks ago saw some 50 people being
hospitalized in Pitas, where one person was dead on arrival at the
district hospital.
Another 17 people were admitted to the Kudat hospital and 15 other
were hospitalized in Kota Marudu, after being found to be infected
with _V. cholerae_. Many of the patients in Kudat were from nearby
villages such as Kampung Tanjung Kapor, Kampung Marabahai, squatter
settlements and islands, including Kampung Mariangin.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Malaysia showing Sabah on the island of Borneo, which is
shared with Indonesia and Brunei, can be found at
<http://www.seasite.niu.edu/seaclub/images/malaysia-map.jpg>. - Mod.LL]
